RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) _ Advance Auto Parts Inc. (AAP) on Monday reported fourth-quarter profit of $81.7 million.The Raleigh, North Carolina-based company said it had profit of $1.30 per share. Earnings, adjusted for one-time gains and costs, were $2.07 per share.The results exceeded Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of nine analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $1.97 per share.The auto parts retailer posted revenue of $2.4 billion in the period, also beating Street forecasts. Six analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $2.36 billion.For the year, the company reported profit of $616.1 million, or $9.55 per share. Revenue was reported as $11 billion.Advance Auto Parts expects full-year earnings in the range of $13.20 to $13.75 per share, with revenue in the range of $11.2 billion to $11.5 billion.Advance Auto Parts shares have decreased 6.5% since the beginning of the year. In the final minutes of trading on Monday, shares hit $224.28, an increase of 47% in the last 12 months.ADVERTISEMENT_____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on AAP at https://www.zacks.com/ap/AAP